We will create few user defined functions to bin data, group, logit transform, calculate weights and mean look proportion respectively.

#binning the data for analysis with 50 ms latency

bin_data = function(timePlot,d1) {
  
  nbins = timePlot/50
  
  d1$bin = NA #creates a new column within the dataframe d for the time bins, which is filled with Not A Number
  binTrial = rep(1:nbins,each=3) 
  lentrials = rle(d1$trialID)$lengths #get length of each trial
  
  ## Loop through trials
  for (i in seq(1,length(lentrials))) # 
  {
    # First sample of trial
    ind = sum(lentrials[1:i-1])+1 # get onset of current trial, i.e. sum the length of previous trials (i-1) and add 1 frame to get first frame
    ind = ind+4 # adjust 60 ms (4 frames) for correction of eye-tracker latency
    
    # add bin column from target start
    d1$bin[ind:(ind+length(binTrial)-1)] = binTrial
  }
  
  # remove all bits not captured by the bin
  d1 = d1[which(d1$bin!="NA"),]

  
  return(d1)
}


#group data by bin,subject,item,voice and path conditions
grp_data = function(df) {
  df_grp <- df %>% 
    group_by(bin, SubjID, ItemID, voice_cond, path_cond) %>%
  dplyr::summarise( 
    SamplesInAOI=sum(AOIhitAlternate))
  df_grp$SamplesTotal <- 3 
  return(df_grp)
}


#empirical logit transformation the fixation proportion
emplog = function(df) {
  df$elog <- with(df, log((SamplesInAOI+0.5)/(SamplesTotal-SamplesInAOI+0.5)))
  return(df)
}

#function to calculate weights
emplogweight = function(df) {
  df$wts<- with(df, 1/(SamplesInAOI+0.5) + 1/(SamplesTotal-SamplesInAOI+0.5))
  return(df)
}

#mean proportion of looks
mean_prop = function(df) {
  df$meanProp <- df$SamplesInAOI/df$SamplesTotal # proportion of looks to the EP (AOI)
  return(df)
}

Subsetting the data to identify the contrastive and non-contrastive sequences by items and binning separately each of them. Adding 3rd order orthogonal polynomial to our data frame and creating factors for further analysis. We will use Growth Curve Analysis (GCA) for fixation proportion analysis.

load('neg_fixation.Rdata')


#identifying the sequences
data_C1<- subset(data_fixation, ItemID == 16 | ItemID == 17 | ItemID == 18 | ItemID == 19 | ItemID == 20)
data_C2<- subset(data_fixation, ItemID == 11 | ItemID == 12 | ItemID == 13 | ItemID == 14 | ItemID == 15)
data_C3<- subset(data_fixation, ItemID == 6 | ItemID == 7 | ItemID == 8 | ItemID == 9 | ItemID == 10)
data_C4<- subset(data_fixation, ItemID == 1 | ItemID == 2 | ItemID == 3 | ItemID == 4 | ItemID == 5)

#binning the data seperately for each sequence
data_binned_C1 <- bin_data(20099, data_C1)  #noncontrastive sequence
data_binned_C4 <- bin_data(26549, data_C4)  #contrastive sequence

#selecting the post-window segment for analysis
data_window_cont <- data_binned_C4[data_binned_C4$bin >=200,]
data_window_ncont <- data_binned_C1[data_binned_C1$bin >=150,]

#re-aligning the bin so that it starts from 1
data_window_cont$bin<- data_window_cont$bin-199
data_window_ncont$bin<- data_window_ncont$bin-149

#final data window
data_window<- rbind(data_window_cont, data_window_ncont)
data_window<-grp_data(data_window)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'bin', 'SubjID', 'ItemID', 'voice_cond'.
## You can override using the `.groups` argument.
#preparing the 3rd degree polynomial
t <- poly(unique(data_window$bin), 3)

#finally adding polynomials to our dataframe 
data_window[,paste("ot", 1:3, sep="")] <- t[data_window$bin, 1:3]

Grouping and adjusting our dependent variables and independent factors.

#calculating emprical logit
grp_df_emp<-emplog(data_window)

# calculating weights
grp_df_emp_wt<-emplogweight(grp_df_emp)

clean_data<- grp_df_emp_wt #our clean binned data on which we will run GCA analysis.


clean_data$voice_cond <- as.factor(clean_data$voice_cond) #factors adjustments by default treatment contrast with 'No Voice' condition as baseline.
clean_data$SubjID <- as.factor(clean_data$SubjID) #subject factor

Fitting the linear model on empirical logit data with fixed effect voice condition and random intercept and slope for linear terms. Unfortunately the random intercept and slopes for orthogonal terms didnt converge so the simplified model is the best we could do.

m.elog_fixation<- lmer(elog ~ (ot1+ot2+ot3)*voice_cond + 
                        (1|SubjID) + (1|SubjID:voice_cond),
                        control=lmerControl(optimizer = "bobyqa"), data=clean_data, weights = 1/wts, REML=F, verbose = 100)
